Turkish Equity Movers: Bimeks Bilgi, TAV Havalimanlari Move

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-04-15T15:04:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/turkish-equity-movers-bimeks-bilgi-tav-havalimanlari-move.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  rose 490.94, or 0.7 percent, to 68,450.44 at the 5:30 p.m.
close in Istanbul. Gains for the week were 0.5 percent.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Bimeks Bilgi Islem & Dis Ticaret AS (BMEKS TI), a consumer
electronics retailer, rose 11 kurus, or 2.4 percent, to 4.64
liras on its second day of trading on the exchange after an
initial public offering.  TAV Havalimanlari Holding AS (TAVHL)  , an airport
operator, gained 10 kurus, or 1.3 percent, to 7.62 liras, the
highest close since April 7, after it was rated “buy” in new
coverage today at Nomura Holdings Inc., with a price estimate of
9.2 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Ankara at 
